commentTextItems.html: and he's done it for a tie flicked down to deep backward square. What a game of cricket!

commentPostTextItems.html: A quite extraordinary match ends in a tie and it's Kevin O'Brien and Paul Stirling who come out with the credit for the Irish with two brilliant innings.
The man who hit the match tying boundary Kevin O'Brien is named man of the match.
Well we will have coverage of the second ODI on Sunday which is now a winner takes all clash.
So join me Conor Hayes for that but from a cold and overcast Clontarf it's goodbye.

milestones.description: This is the highest match aggregate (541) involving teams Pakistan & Ireland in ODIs
Kevin O'Brien has become the top scorer for IRE in ODIs with 1833 runs, going past Porterfield's 1752

stories.title: Ireland would consider Pakistan tour

stories.summary: Ireland would be willing to tour Pakistan if security assurances were met,  Cricket Ireland chief executive Warren Deutrom has said.
